$\mathrm{K}_{\mathrm{a}}$ of Butyric acid $\Rightarrow 2 \times 10^{-5} \,\mathrm{PKa}=4.7$ <br/><br/>$\mathrm{pH}$ of $0.2 \mathrm{M}$ solution,<br/><br/>
$$
\mathrm{pH}=\frac{1}{2} \mathrm{pK}_{\mathrm{a}}-\frac{1}{2} \log \mathrm{C}
$$<br/><br/>
$$
\begin{aligned}
&=\frac{1}{2}(4 \cdot 7) - \frac{1}{2} \log (0.2) \\\\
&=2.35+0.35=2.7
\end{aligned}
$$<br/><br/>
$$
\mathrm{pH}=27 \times 10^{-1}
$$
